# Plugin standards

**Naming:** Slug = lowercase hyphenated functional name (e.g. `engineer-move-serials`, `woo-product-search` — not `woocommerce-product-search`). Woo-related plugins: display **Woo** not **WooCommerce** in names; slug prefix **`woo-`**. See **plugin-naming.mdc** and `.tools/chameleon-plugin-manifest.json`.

**Deploy:** Installed path `wp-content/plugins/<slug>/`; main file `<slug>.php` in that folder. Zip: one top-level folder = slug; contents = plugin files. Store zips in **`dist/<slug>/`** (or `plugins/dist/<slug>/` in multi-plugin repos). Build script in `scripts/` (e.g. `build-zip.ps1`); run after any plugin change. **PHP must be UTF-8 without BOM** — see **plugin-no-utf8-bom.mdc**; `Build-PluginInstallZip` fails if BOM is present.

**Version:** MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH. **PATCH** on every change: update `VERSION` file, CHANGELOG entry, main file Version header in same commit. **MINOR** for new features; **MAJOR** for explicit new release. Never commit a version bump without a changelog entry.

**Zip retention:** Keep 5 most recent + all X.0.0 zips. Script `.\scripts\cleanup-plugin-zips.ps1`; run from project root. Build script should call cleanup after each build. See plugin-zip-retention.mdc for policy.

**Update URI (required):** Every Chameleon plugin main PHP file must include `Update URI: https://admin.chameleoncodewing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/plugin-repo` (after `Plugin URI`; same URL on all plugins). Sites need **(Chameleon) Chameleon Admin** for updates from `plugins-live` / `index.json`. Audit or backfill: `.\scripts\add-chameleon-update-uri.ps1`.

**Chameleon Admin (required):** Every `(Chameleon)` product plugin except `chameleon-admin` must require **(Chameleon) Chameleon Admin** before activation (`Requires Plugins: chameleon-admin` + `includes/chameleon-require-admin.php`). See **chameleon-admin-required.mdc** and `.\scripts\wire-chameleon-admin-dependency.ps1`.
